This paper is about Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO), which is a popular optimization algorithm in the field of computational intelligence. The paper proposes a variant of PSO that uses self-adaptive potential-based stopping criteria to improve the efficiency of the algorithm. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because PSO is a type of evolutionary algorithm, and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because optimization is a common problem in AI. It could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) because PSO is a type of optimization algorithm used in machine learning. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) because optimization is a common problem in control systems, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because PSO is an algorithm used for optimization.
